1 (2) At least thirty days before entering into an agreement with a
2 consumer for a renewable energy system or battery energy storage system,
3 a renewable energy sales company shall provide a consumer with the
4 following written statements on separate forms in a font no smaller than
5 twelve points:
6 (a) Estimates of cost savings are based upon calculations from the
7 previous twelve months of utility bills, or, if twelve months of utility
8 bills are not available, a reasonable estimate of cost savings. The
9 assumptions, such as the rates a utility charges for electricity, that
10 are used to estimate the cost savings may change. There may be utility
